Charles Chaisler, a professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, developed a course that he believed was the first of its kind in the United States.
After his discovery, he was caught up in the idea of introducing such a course, giving a preliminary report on the impact of sleep deprivation on learning processes.
