The last death penalty in a federal case in New York City was imposed in 1953 on Julius and Ethel Rosenberg, a couple executed for conspiracy to spy on the Soviet Union during the Cold War two years earlier.
Rosenbergs were executed using an electric chair on 19 June 1953.
